10 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; making
certain acts unlawful; providing penalties; providing
11 forfeiture actions for seized property; providing for
codification; and declaring an emergency.
12
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1796 of Title 21, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 Any alien or person who is not a citizen of the United States
20 who has unlawfully acquired title to or owns land in this state
21 either directly or indirectly through a business entity, trust, or
22 foreign government enterprise, and who uses such land to commit a
23 felony offense in violation of state law shall, upon conviction, be
24 guilty of a felony punishable by imprisonment in the custody of the
Req. No. 16794 Page 1

1 Depa rtment of Corrections for a term not to exceed five (5) years,
2 or by a fine not to exceed One Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00), or by
3 both such fine and imprisonment. In addition, all property seized
4 pursuant to this section shall be subject to the forfeiture
5 provisions provided for in Section 1738 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma
6 Statutes.
7 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
8 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
9 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
10 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
